On March 23, 2020, UW Medicine released an initial COVID-19 testing algorithm for preoperative surgical patients (figure 1
). This algorithm distinguishes whether a surgery was emergent or not and then, based on SC2 test results, recommends appropriate PPE. The second and current iteration of the COVID-19 testing algorithm was released on March 31, 2020 (see figures 2
a for inpatients and 2b for clinic patients). Of note, given the rapidly evolving recommendation of managing operative treatment in the COVID-19 era, as of April 20, 2019, this algorithm has not changed.
